      "content_html": "<img src=\"https://www.sciencedaily.com/images/1920/ozempic-wegovy-rybelsus-semaglutide-medications.webp\" style=\"width:100%;max-height:300px;object-fit:cover;\" />\nA new analysis is raising concerns about Wegovy, the blockbuster weight-loss drug, after researchers found it may carry the highest risk of a rare “eye stroke” that can cause sudden vision loss. The study, based on millions of FDA side-effect reports, found the risk signal was nearly five times stronger for Wegovy than for Ozempic, despite both containing semaglutide.",
